### Subagent 1: Tautological & Trivially-Passing Tests

```
Audit this test suite for tests that always pass regardless of implementation correctness.

Tech stack: [from Phase 1]
Test files: [from Phase 1]

## TAUTOLOGICAL ASSERTIONS (Critical)
A tautological test asserts exactly what was set up — it tests Eloquent/the framework, not our code.

Examples (Pest/PHP):
```php
// BAD: just tests that Eloquent stores what you set
$user = User::factory()->create(['name' => 'John']);
expect($user->name)->toBe('John');

// BAD: tests the factory, not business logic
$order = Order::factory()->create(['status' => 'pending']);
expect($order->status)->toBe('pending');

// GOOD: tests that our code transforms or validates something
$order = Order::factory()->create();
$order->complete();
expect($order->status)->toBe('completed')
    ->and($order->completed_at)->not->toBeNull();
```

Examples (JavaScript):
```typescript
// BAD: always true
expect(1 + 1).toBe(2);
expect(user.id).toBe(user.id);

// BAD: just tests assignment
const obj = { name: 'test' };
expect(obj.name).toBe('test');
```

## SELF-REFERENTIAL ASSERTIONS (High)
Tests that compare a value to itself or to a value derived from the same call:
```php
// BAD
expect($user->full_name)->toBe($user->first_name . ' ' . $user->last_name);
// This always passes — it's just reimplementing the accessor in the test

// GOOD
expect($user->full_name)->toBe('John Doe'); // hardcoded expected value
```

## ASSERTION-ON-INPUT (High)
Tests that assert on data they directly controlled:
```php
// BAD: asserts on data we just passed in
$response = $this->post('/users', ['email' => 'test@example.com']);
$response->assertJson(['email' => 'test@example.com']);
// This only verifies the response echoes back the input, not that it was stored or processed

// GOOD
$response = $this->post('/users', ['email' => 'test@example.com']);
assertDatabaseHas('users', ['email' => 'test@example.com']);
```

## MAGIC NUMBER TESTS (Medium)
Tests where the "expected" value is the same magic number used in the production code:
```php
// If production code has: const MAX_RETRIES = 3;
// And test has: expect($job->tries)->toBe(3); // just mirrors the constant
// This doesn't protect against the constant changing to a bad value
```

For each finding, report:
- file:line reference
- The test name
- Why it's tautological
- What meaningful assertion should replace it
- Severity: Critical (always passes) / High (rarely catches bugs) / Medium (low signal)
```

