### Subagent 3: Over-Mocked & Fake-Heavy Tests

```
Audit this test suite for tests so reliant on mocks that the real application logic is never exercised.

Tech stack: [from Phase 1]
Test files: [from Phase 1]

## MOCK-HEAVY TESTS (High)
When more than 50% of the test setup is mocking behavior, the test often becomes a test of the mock configuration, not the code:

```php
// BAD: every dependency is mocked — the actual logic path is untested
it('processes the payment', function () {
    $gateway = Mockery::mock(PaymentGateway::class);
    $gateway->shouldReceive('charge')->andReturn(true);
    $notifier = Mockery::mock(Notifier::class);
    $notifier->shouldReceive('send')->once();
    $logger = Mockery::mock(Logger::class);
    $logger->shouldReceive('info')->once();

    $processor = new PaymentProcessor($gateway, $notifier, $logger);
    $processor->process($amount);
    // Everything is mocked — if the actual PaymentGateway is broken, this still passes
});

// BETTER: Only mock external I/O, test real logic
it('processes the payment', function () {
    Http::fake(['stripe.com/*' => Http::response(['status' => 'succeeded'], 200)]);
    $order = Order::factory()->create();
    $order->processPayment();
    expect($order->fresh()->status)->toBe('paid');
});
```

## MOCKING ELOQUENT / ORM (Critical)
Mocking the database instead of using real test databases creates dangerous divergence:
```php
// BAD: Eloquent is mocked — schema changes, relationships, scopes all invisible
$user = Mockery::mock(User::class);
$user->shouldReceive('find')->andReturn(new User(['id' => 1]));
```

Prefer `RefreshDatabase` with real factories over mocking models.

## VERIFYING MOCKS NOT BEHAVIOR (High)
Tests that only verify that a method was called, without checking what it did:
```php
// BAD: only proves the method was called, not that the outcome is correct
$mailer->shouldReceive('send')->once();
// What was sent? Was it the right email? Right recipient?

// GOOD
Mail::fake();
Mail::assertSent(OrderConfirmation::class, function ($mail) use ($order) {
    return $mail->hasTo($order->customer->email)
        && $mail->order->id === $order->id;
});
```

## FAKE OVERUSE IN FEATURE TESTS (Medium)
Feature tests that fake so much they become unit tests in disguise:
- Multiple `Event::fake()` without asserting on events
- `Queue::fake()` but never asserting jobs were dispatched with correct data
- `Storage::fake()` but never verifying file contents

For each finding, report:
- file:line reference
- Test name
- What is mocked vs what is real
- What real failure modes this test would miss
- Recommendation: move to integration test, or refine assertions
```

