### Subagent 5: Duplicate Tests & Dataset Abuse

```
Audit this test suite for redundant tests that provide no additional coverage.

Tech stack: [from Phase 1]
Test files: [from Phase 1]

## EXACT DUPLICATE TESTS (High)
Tests with different names but identical setup, action, and assertion:
```php
// These two tests are identical in behavior:
it('stores the user', function () {
    $data = ['name' => 'John', 'email' => 'john@example.com'];
    $this->post('/users', $data)->assertCreated();
});

it('creates a new user successfully', function () {
    $data = ['name' => 'Jane', 'email' => 'jane@example.com'];
    $this->post('/users', $data)->assertCreated();
});
// Both test POST /users with valid data — same coverage, different fixture values
```

## DATASET ABUSE (Medium)
`->with()` / `@dataProvider` datasets that vary input but all exercise the same code path:
```php
// BAD: all of these are valid emails — they all go through the same path
it('accepts valid email', function (string $email) {
    $this->post('/register', ['email' => $email])->assertCreated();
})->with(['a@b.com', 'test@example.com', 'user+tag@domain.org', 'x@y.z']);
// Having 4 valid email variants adds no new coverage — 1 is enough

// GOOD: dataset tests different BEHAVIORS, not different fixture values
it('handles email', function (string $email, int $expectedStatus) {
    $this->post('/register', ['email' => $email])->assertStatus($expectedStatus);
})->with([
    'valid email' => ['user@example.com', 201],
    'missing @ sign' => ['notanemail', 422],
    'missing domain' => ['user@', 422],
    'empty string' => ['', 422],
]);
```

## NEAR-DUPLICATE TESTS ACROSS FILES (Medium)
Same scenario tested in both Feature and Unit tests with identical coverage:
- If a feature test already fully covers a scenario end-to-end, a unit test for the same scenario adds no value

## REDUNDANT ARCHITECTURE TESTS (Medium, Pest-specific)
Architecture tests checking for classes/patterns that no longer exist in the project:
```php
// BAD: if there are no Repository classes, this test is vacuously true
arch('repositories extend BaseRepository')
    ->expect('App\Repositories')
    ->toExtend(BaseRepository::class);
// Passes because the namespace is empty, not because the rule is followed
```

How to detect:
1. Find all `arch()` tests
2. For each namespace referenced, check if any classes actually exist there
3. Flag `arch()` tests where the target namespace has zero classes

## MIRRORED INVERSE TESTS WITHOUT INDEPENDENCE (Low)
```php
// These two tests will always agree — if one fails, both fail
it('returns true for active users', fn() => expect(User::factory()->active()->create()->isActive())->toBeTrue());
it('returns false for inactive users', fn() => expect(User::factory()->inactive()->create()->isActive())->toBeFalse());
// If isActive() always returns true, the second test catches it — this pairing IS valuable
// Flag ONLY when the two tests use the same factory state
```

For each finding, report:
- file:line references (both/all duplicates)
- Why they're duplicant (same path, same assertion, different fixture values)
- Which test to keep, which to remove or transform
- Suggestion: consolidate with dataset, or replace one with an edge-case test
```

